law.catch_line: Provisions inconsistent with federal law unenforceable.
law.text: Any provision of this chapter which is set forth as inconsistent with the provisions of Public Law 95-87 by the Secretary of the Interior pursuant to Section 505(b) of that act shall be deemed superseded by federal law and shall thereafter be unenforceable by the Commonwealth of Kentucky.

metadata.lrc-note: The provisions of this section became operative on May 18, 1982, when the conditional approval granted by the United States Secretary of the Interior appeared in the Federal Register.
